{"title_page": "Edurmaneli Ganda Pakkadmaneli Hendthi", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{more citations needed|date=January 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox film|\n| name = Edurmaneli Ganda Pakkadmaneli Hendthi\n| image = \n| caption =\n| director = [[Relangi Narasimha Rao]]\n| writer = Relangi Narasimha Rao\n| screenplay = Relangi Narasimha Rao\n| based on = ''[[Edurinti Mogudu Pakkinti Pellam]]'' (1991)\n| starring = [[Shashikumar]] <br> [[Shruti (actress)|Shruti]] <br> [[Umashree]] <br> [[Mukhyamantri Chandru]] <br> Master Adithya\n| producer = P. Balaram\n| music = [[Raj-Koti]]\n| cinematography = Sharath\n| editing = Murali <br> Ramayya\n| studio = Sri Anupama Productions\n| released = {{film date|df=yes|1992|4|20|}}\n| runtime = 136&nbsp;minutes\n| language = Kannada\n| country = India\n| budget =\n}}\n\n'''''Edurmaneli Ganda Pakkadmaneli Hendthi''''' (English: '''Opposite House Husband-Side House Wife''') is a 1992 Indian [[Kannada language|Kannada]] [[comedy film|comedy drama]] film directed by [[Relangi Narasimha Rao]] and produced by P. Balaram. A remake of Rao's [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film, ''[[Edurinti Mogudu Pakkinti Pellam]]'' (1991), the film featured [[Shashikumar]], [[Shruti (actress)|Shruti]] and [[Baladitya (actor)|Master Adithya]] in the lead roles.<ref name=\"chiloka\">{{cite web|url=http://chiloka.com/movie/edurmaneli-ganda-pakkadmaneli-hendthi-1992 |publisher=chiloka.com|title=Edurmaneli Ganda Pakkadmaneli Hendthi (1992) Kannada movie: Watch online |accessdate=2016-09-27}}</ref>  The film's music was composed by [[Raj-Koti]] and cinematography is by Sharath.\n\n==Plot==\nBagalkote Vasudevarao (BaVa) is a big miser and marries Jaya, who likes to lead a normal and enjoyable life. Due to her husband's constant miserly attitude in everyday life and a publicly embarrassing event, she leaves the house being pregnant. After a few years she rents a house which unknowingly for her is right next to that of her estranged husband's house. she is living with her now school going kid, who seems to have inherited all the stingy qualities of his father. The child gets closer to his father with everyday interactions which makes his mother Jaya much worried and leads to her shifting to a new house. Meanwhile, Bava's mother, who was angry with him because of his marriage against her will, gets to know he has left his wife. She joins as a maid in Jaya's house to spend time with Jaya and her grandson. Eventually, Jaya discovers the maid is none other than her mother-in-law and feels bad for treating her as a maid. Bava and Jaya's Nepali Boss Rekha (who is known for her hilarious Malapropisms, much to the discomfort of her colleagues), a kind-hearted lady, concots a plan to rid of Bava's stinginess  leading to a situation where Bava is admitted to the hospital and he is made to believe that he has an incurable brain tumor and very little time to live. As per these plan of events Bava's view towards money and family is changed and unites him with his family. In the end, Rekha reveals the plot and the movie ends on a happy note.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Shashikumar]] as Bava alias Bagalkote Vasudeva rao \n* [[Shruti (actress)|Shruti]] as Jayakumari \n* [[Mukhyamantri Chandru]] As Turuvekere Nethrappa\n* [[Umashree]] as Kanakaveni, a novelist \n* [[Mysore Lokesh]] as Kariyanna \n* [[Baladitya (actor)|Master Adithya]] as Anand alias Aa / Stampu\n* [[M. S. Umesh]] as Thippayya \n* Bangalore Nagesh as Sandeharao \n* [[Annapoorna (actress)|Annapoorna]] as Bava's mother \n* [[Rekha Das|Rekha Das ]] as Municipality Commissioner Rekha Koirala \n* Manju Malini as Bala kumari \n\n== Soundtrack ==\nThe music of the film was composed by [[Raj-Koti]] with lyrics by [[R. N. Jayagopal]].<ref name=\"mp3to\">{{cite web|url=http://mp3to.co.in/music-search/yadurmane-ganda-pakkadmane-hendthi-kannada-movie-songs-kannu-bithu-shashik/a6f7e79ec4/ |publisher=mp3to.co.in|title=Yadurmane Ganda Pakkadmane Hendthi Kannada Movie Songs Kannu Bithu Shashik|accessdate=2016-09-27}}</ref>\n\n{{track listing\n| headline = Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| collapsed = no\n| title1 = Ammayya Ammayya\n| extra1 = [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]] & [[Manjula Gururaj]]\n| lyrics1 = [[R. N. Jayagopal]]\n| length1 = \n| title2 = Meghavu Hariside\n| extra2 = S. P. Balasubrahmanyam & [[K. S. Chithra]]\n| lyrics2 = R. N. Jayagopal\n| length2 = \n| title3 = Lamba Chikka\n| extra3 = [[Malgudi Subha]]\n| lyrics3 = R. N. Jayagopal\n| length3 = \n| title4 = Kannu Bitthu \n| extra4 = S. P. Balasubrahmanyam & Manjula Gururaj\n| lyrics4 = R. N. Jayagopal\n| length4 = \n| title5 = Ek Do Teen\n| extra5 = S. P. Balasubrahmanyam & Manjula Gururaj\n| lyrics5 = R. N. Jayagopal\n| length5 = \n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Relangi Narasimha Rao}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Edurmaneli Ganda Pakkadmaneli Hendthi}}\n[[Category:1992 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:1990s Kannada-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:1990s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Kannada remakes of Telugu films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Raj-Koti]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Relangi Narasimha Rao]]\n\n\n{{1990s-Kannada-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{more citations needed|date=January 2017}}\n\n{{Infobox film|\n| name = Edurmaneli Ganda Pakkadmaneli Hendthi\n| image = \n| caption =\n| director = [[Relangi Narasimha Rao]]\n| writer = Relangi Narasimha Rao\n| screenplay = Relangi Narasimha Rao\n| based on = ''[[Edurinti Mogudu Pakkinti Pellam]]'' (1991)\n| starring = [[Shashikumar]] <br> [[Shruti (actress)|Shruti]] <br> [[Umashree]] <br> [[Mukhyamantri Chandru]] <br> Master Adithya\n| producer = P. Balaram\n| music = [[Raj-Koti]]\n| cinematography = Sharath\n| editing = Murali <br> Ramayya\n| studio = Sri Anupama Productions\n| released = {{film date|df=yes|1992|4|20|}}\n| runtime = 136&nbsp;minutes\